Assert.AreNotSame(original, clone);
```

#### 7. `Serialize_ThenDeserialize_ProducesOriginal` (line 9–16) — Minor: Assert Against Literals

This round-trip test is legitimate — serialization round-trips *should* be identity. However, asserting `input.Name == output.Name` means a bug where both are `null` would pass silently. Prefer one assertion against a literal:

```csharp
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", output.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(30, output.Age);
```

